def: Not assuming; not bold or forward; not arrogant or presuming;humble; modest; retiring; as, an unassuming youth; unassumingmanners.
Indulging one's appetites, desires, etc., freely.
Time characterized by syncopation, as in many negro melodies.[Colloq.]
Pertaining, or given, to swooning; fainting.
To remove the glaze from, as pottery or porcelain, so as togive a dull finish.
The quality or state of being pertinacious; obstinacy;perseverance; persistency. Macaulay.

The encampment on one of the principal passages round a placebesieged, to prevent relief and intercept convoys.(i) (Naut.) The after-part of a vessel's side, generallycorresponding in extent with the quarter-deck; also, the part of theyardarm outside of the slings.(j) (Her.) One of the divisions of an escutcheon when it is dividedinto four portions by a horizontal and a perpendicular line meetingin the fess point.
